        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Sept 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.—</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I am quite delighted at all you say &amp; propose.—</p>
<p>Pray send the sheets to Lyell. Unfortunately the part most likely to be interesting to him is not ready.—</p>
<p>Up to p. 240 is completed: could not 3 following sheets be sent, they only want another glance by me, as they have been revised once. One copy of my two copies of the 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> Revises of these 3 sheets could be sent.—</p>
<p>With hearty thanks | In Haste to catch Post.— | Yours very sincerely | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">3.2 have] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> <hi rend="italic">illeg</hi></note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n2">3.2 copy] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n3">3.2 two copies of the 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 3.3] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>
        
    
        
